[
  {
    "order": 0,
    "start": 0,
    "end": 3.12,
    "text": "This is a download from BBC Learning English.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 1,
    "start": 3.12,
    "end": 5.6,
    "text": "To find out more, visit our website.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 2,
    "start": 5.6,
    "end": 8.24,
    "text": "6 Minute English",
    "speaker": "Neil"
  },
  {
    "order": 3,
    "start": 8.24,
    "end": 10.4,
    "text": "From BBC Learning English",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 4,
    "start": 11.2,
    "end": 13.359,
    "text": "Hello and welcome to 6 Minute English,",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 5,
    "start": 13.359,
    "end": 15.919,
    "text": "the programme where we bring you an interesting topic",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 6,
    "start": 15.919,
    "end": 18.08,
    "text": "and six items of vocabulary.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 7,
    "start": 18.08,
    "end": 21.039,
    "text": "I'm Neil, today we're talking about jobs.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 8,
    "start": 21.039,
    "end": 22.08,
    "text": "And I'm Dan.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 9,
    "start": 22.08,
    "end": 24.08,
    "text": "And specifically we're looking at the trend",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 10,
    "start": 24.08,
    "end": 25.92,
    "text": "for having more than one job.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 11,
    "start": 25.92,
    "end": 27.92,
    "text": "Yes. On that note – Dan",
    "speaker": "Neil"
  },
  {
    "order": 12,
    "start": 27.92,
    "end": 30.32,
    "text": "will you ever ask this question as a kid,",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 13,
    "start": 30.32,
    "end": 32.48,
    "text": "what do you want to be when you grow up?",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 14,
    "start": 32.48,
    "end": 34.079,
    "text": "Do you remember your answer?",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 15,
    "start": 34.079,
    "end": 35.52,
    "text": "I wanted to be a ninja turtle.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 16,
    "start": 36.88,
    "end": 37.52,
    "text": "And you?",
    "speaker": "Dan"
  },
  {
    "order": 17,
    "start": 37.52,
    "end": 38.64,
    "text": "doesn’t surprise me.",
    "speaker": "portfolio"
  },
  {
    "order": 18,
    "start": 38.64,
    "end": 40.8,
    "text": "I think I wanted to be a professional footballer.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 19,
    "start": 40.8,
    "end": 42.079,
    "text": "I wanted to play for England.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 20,
    "start": 42.079,
    "end": 42.96,
    "text": "Hmm.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 21,
    "start": 42.96,
    "end": 45.439,
    "text": "Well, for many people, that question gets harder",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 22,
    "start": 45.439,
    "end": 46.88,
    "text": "the older they become.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 23,
    "start": 46.88,
    "end": 48.96,
    "text": "It's one reason why more and more people",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 24,
    "start": 48.96,
    "end": 52.24,
    "text": "have what we call Portfolio careers these days",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 25,
    "start": 52.24,
    "end": 54.4,
    "text": "so they can do a bit of everything.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 26,
    "start": 54.479,
    "end": 57.119,
    "text": "A Portfolio as a noun means a case",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 27,
    "start": 57.119,
    "end": 58.96,
    "text": "for carrying large pictures.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 28,
    "start": 58.96,
    "end": 62,
    "text": "Or it can mean the collection of pictures themselves.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 29,
    "start": 62,
    "end": 64.079,
    "text": "But we also use it as an adjective",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 30,
    "start": 64.079,
    "end": 66.239,
    "text": "to describe groups of certain things.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 31,
    "start": 66.239,
    "end": 67.759,
    "text": "In this case, careers.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 32,
    "start": 67.759,
    "end": 68.48,
    "text": "Indeed,",
    "speaker": "portfolio"
  },
  {
    "order": 33,
    "start": 68.48,
    "end": 71.2,
    "text": "We could say someone who is a part-time teacher",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 34,
    "start": 71.2,
    "end": 75.039,
    "text": "and a part-time musician has a Portfolio career.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 35,
    "start": 75.039,
    "end": 76.4,
    "text": "Sounds like a good combination.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 36,
    "start": 76.959,
    "end": 78.799,
    "text": "First, let's do today's question.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 37,
    "start": 78.799,
    "end": 79.759,
    "text": "It's job-related.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 38,
    "start": 80.48,
    "end": 84.159,
    "text": "Many surnames in English originally come from professions.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 39,
    "start": 84.159,
    "end": 85.92,
    "text": "The surname Baker, for example,",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 40,
    "start": 85.92,
    "end": 89.679,
    "text": "was originally given to people who worked as da da da,",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 41,
    "start": 89.679,
    "end": 90.399,
    "text": "bakers.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 42,
    "start": 90.879,
    "end": 92.879,
    "text": "But what about the surname Bond",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 43,
    "start": 92.879,
    "end": 95.519,
    "text": "as in 007 James Bond?",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 44,
    "start": 95.519,
    "end": 97.359,
    "text": "Who had this surname?",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 45,
    "start": 97.359,
    "end": 101.519,
    "text": "Was it A, farmers, B, spies, or C, guards?",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 46,
    "start": 101.519,
    "end": 103.199,
    "text": "It can't be spies, can it?",
    "speaker": "Dan"
  },
  {
    "order": 47,
    "start": 103.199,
    "end": 106.319,
    "text": "So I'm going to guess guards C.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 48,
    "start": 106.319,
    "end": 106.799,
    "text": "Great,",
    "speaker": "Dan"
  },
  {
    "order": 49,
    "start": 106.799,
    "end": 108.799,
    "text": "Well, let's find out at the end of the program.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 50,
    "start": 108.799,
    "end": 110.56,
    "text": "Now, the Portfolio career.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 51,
    "start": 110.56,
    "end": 113.519,
    "text": "Emily Wappnick is the Canadian author of a book",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 52,
    "start": 113.519,
    "end": 115.439,
    "text": "called How to Be Everything,",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 53,
    "start": 115.439,
    "end": 118.959,
    "text": "a guide for those who still don't know what they want to be",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 54,
    "start": 118.959,
    "end": 120.079,
    "text": "when they grow up.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 55,
    "start": 120.079,
    "end": 123.92,
    "text": "Which specific example of a portfolio career does she mention?",
    "speaker": "portfolio"
  },
  {
    "order": 56,
    "start": 123.92,
    "end": 126.879,
    "text": "More and more people are doing multiple things",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 57,
    "start": 126.879,
    "end": 128.319,
    "text": "and multiple jobs.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 58,
    "start": 128.319,
    "end": 130,
    "text": "And it's not just to make ends meet.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 59,
    "start": 130,
    "end": 132.079,
    "text": "A lot of people are choosing this kind of lifestyle.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 60,
    "start": 132.079,
    "end": 134.879,
    "text": "They've got three different businesses",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 61,
    "start": 134.879,
    "end": 136.479,
    "text": "that are just thriving,",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 62,
    "start": 136.479,
    "end": 138.56,
    "text": "or they're a serial entrepreneur,",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 63,
    "start": 138.56,
    "end": 140.96,
    "text": "or they've got a career in two different areas.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 64,
    "start": 140.96,
    "end": 144,
    "text": "There is a guy that I mentioned who is a psychotherapist",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 65,
    "start": 144,
    "end": 145.599,
    "text": "and a lootheer.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 66,
    "start": 145.599,
    "end": 147.439,
    "text": "He makes violins,",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 67,
    "start": 147.439,
    "end": 149.6,
    "text": "and he is very successful in both.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 68,
    "start": 149.6,
    "end": 152.319,
    "text": "Emily is clearly a fan of this kind of working.",
    "speaker": "Neil"
  },
  {
    "order": 69,
    "start": 152.319,
    "end": 155.28,
    "text": "She says she knows a man who's both a psychotherapist",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 70,
    "start": 155.28,
    "end": 158.159,
    "text": "and a lootheer, someone who makes violins.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 71,
    "start": 158.159,
    "end": 161.92,
    "text": "She says this trend is more than just about working to make ends meet.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 72,
    "start": 161.92,
    "end": 164.879,
    "text": "In other words, working to make enough money to live.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 73,
    "start": 164.879,
    "end": 167.2,
    "text": "And she used another interesting expression,",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 74,
    "start": 167.2,
    "end": 168.96,
    "text": "a serial entrepreneur.",
    "speaker": "entrepreneurserialserialkillerserialmurderer"
  },
  {
    "order": 75,
    "start": 168.96,
    "end": 170.08,
    "text": "What's that exactly?",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 76,
    "start": 170.16,
    "end": 174.08,
    "text": "Well, an entrepreneur is someone who starts and runs businesses.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 77,
    "start": 174.08,
    "end": 176.96,
    "text": "And the use of serial here as an adjective",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 78,
    "start": 176.96,
    "end": 180.24,
    "text": "describes someone who does the same thing again and again.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 79,
    "start": 180.24,
    "end": 182.96,
    "text": "Though we should say the adjective is more often used",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 80,
    "start": 182.96,
    "end": 184.56,
    "text": "for criminal activity,",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 81,
    "start": 184.56,
    "end": 187.6,
    "text": "such as a serial killer or serial murderer.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 82,
    "start": 187.6,
    "end": 191.28,
    "text": "Yeah, not the kind of portfolio career I had in mind.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 83,
    "start": 191.28,
    "end": 193.439,
    "text": "A serial entrepreneur, on the other hand,",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 84,
    "start": 193.439,
    "end": 195.92,
    "text": "starts and runs business after business.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 85,
    "start": 195.92,
    "end": 198.88,
    "text": "Another thing, because Emily believes the world of work",
    "speaker": "add another string to your bow"
  },
  {
    "order": 86,
    "start": 199.039,
    "end": 203.199,
    "text": "is changing fast, it's sensible to be able to do more than one thing.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 87,
    "start": 203.199,
    "end": 207.039,
    "text": "In other words, it's wise to add another string to your bow.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 88,
    "start": 207.039,
    "end": 212,
    "text": "A great phrase, which really just means to learn new skills you can use in the future.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 89,
    "start": 212,
    "end": 213.68,
    "text": "I'd like to learn Japanese.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 90,
    "start": 213.68,
    "end": 215.68,
    "text": "That would add another string to my bow.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 91,
    "start": 215.68,
    "end": 216.56,
    "text": "So does me.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 92,
    "start": 217.359,
    "end": 221.199,
    "text": "But choosing a portfolio career is not for everyone, of course.",
    "speaker": "portfolio"
  },
  {
    "order": 93,
    "start": 221.199,
    "end": 223.439,
    "text": "It often simply comes down to money.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 94,
    "start": 223.439,
    "end": 225.919,
    "text": "He is Charles Handy, writer and philosopher,",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 95,
    "start": 225.919,
    "end": 229.759,
    "text": "and the man who popularised the term portfolio career in the first place.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 96,
    "start": 230.399,
    "end": 233.28,
    "text": "80% of the people at corporate jobs hate them.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 97,
    "start": 233.28,
    "end": 235.519,
    "text": "Oh, I'm dissatisfied with them.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 98,
    "start": 235.519,
    "end": 237.359,
    "text": "Whereas if you're doing your own thing,",
    "speaker": "corporate"
  },
  {
    "order": 99,
    "start": 237.359,
    "end": 242.079,
    "text": "80% of them really like the freedom and the entrepreneurial spirit,",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 100,
    "start": 242.079,
    "end": 244,
    "text": "even if they're not making an awful lot of money.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 101,
    "start": 244,
    "end": 245.759,
    "text": "It's a balancing job, really.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 102,
    "start": 245.759,
    "end": 247.759,
    "text": "You're free, but you're poor.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 103,
    "start": 247.759,
    "end": 250.239,
    "text": "Oh, you're slaved, but you're richer.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 104,
    "start": 250.239,
    "end": 251.919,
    "text": "Sounds like a difficult choice.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 105,
    "start": 251.919,
    "end": 254,
    "text": "Be poor or be a slave.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 106,
    "start": 254,
    "end": 255.359,
    "text": "What would you choose, then?",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 107,
    "start": 255.44,
    "end": 257.68,
    "text": "I’d rather be poor and free, thank you very much.",
    "speaker": "Dan"
  },
  {
    "order": 108,
    "start": 257.68,
    "end": 259.84,
    "text": "Well, let's explain a term he used.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 109,
    "start": 259.84,
    "end": 261.04,
    "text": "A corporate job.",
    "speaker": "corporate"
  },
  {
    "order": 110,
    "start": 261.04,
    "end": 262.639,
    "text": "What does corporate mean?",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 111,
    "start": 262.639,
    "end": 266,
    "text": "Quite literally, it's the adjective from the term corporation.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 112,
    "start": 266,
    "end": 268.639,
    "text": "A corporate job is a job at a big corporation,",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 113,
    "start": 268.639,
    "end": 270.4,
    "text": "company or organisation.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 114,
    "start": 270.4,
    "end": 273.52,
    "text": "Usually well paid and with certain benefits.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 115,
    "start": 273.52,
    "end": 276.319,
    "text": "Could we say James Bond has a corporate career?",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 116,
    "start": 276.319,
    "end": 277.36,
    "text": "Hmm.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 117,
    "start": 277.36,
    "end": 278.4,
    "text": "Yes, I guess so!",
    "speaker": "Dan"
  },
  {
    "order": 118,
    "start": 278.4,
    "end": 281.36,
    "text": "And thank you for reminding me to answer today's question,",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 119,
    "start": 281.36,
    "end": 284.4,
    "text": "which profession does the surname Bond come from?",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 120,
    "start": 284.479,
    "end": 287.359,
    "text": "And I said the bonds were guards.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 121,
    "start": 287.359,
    "end": 289.199,
    "text": "I’m afraid you were wrong.",
    "speaker": "Dan"
  },
  {
    "order": 122,
    "start": 289.199,
    "end": 291.359,
    "text": "Bonds were originally peasant farmers",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 123,
    "start": 291.359,
    "end": 293.919,
    "text": "who were bound to work for a particular lord.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 124,
    "start": 293.919,
    "end": 296.799,
    "text": "This word goes back over 1,000 years.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 125,
    "start": 296.799,
    "end": 299.039,
    "text": "The spying game came much later.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 126,
    "start": 299.039,
    "end": 299.839,
    "text": "Indeed.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 127,
    "start": 299.839,
    "end": 302.879,
    "text": "Let's spy today's words once more.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 128,
    "start": 302.879,
    "end": 306.159,
    "text": "We had portfolio, which can be used in different ways.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 129,
    "start": 306.159,
    "end": 309.359,
    "text": "There's a portfolio career as well as the original meaning",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 130,
    "start": 309.359,
    "end": 311.439,
    "text": "of a portfolio of art.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 131,
    "start": 311.439,
    "end": 312.319,
    "text": "Any others?",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 132,
    "start": 312.319,
    "end": 315.599,
    "text": "Yes, people talk about a portfolio of investments ",
    "speaker": "portfolio"
  },
  {
    "order": 133,
    "start": 315.599,
    "end": 318.879,
    "text": "When you invest in several companies at once to reduce the risk.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 134,
    "start": 318.879,
    "end": 322.159,
    "text": "Talking of money, we had to make ends meet.",
    "speaker": null
  },
  {
    "order": 135,
    "start": 322.159,
    "end": 325.04,
